In re CLEMENT, State Excise Com’r. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, Second Department. April 24, 1908.) Appeal from Special Term. In the matter of the petition of Maynard N. Clement, as State Commissioner of Excise, for an order revoking and canceling liquor tax certificate No. 24,302, issued to Julius N. Burr. From an order revoking the certificate, the certificate holder appeals. Affirmed.

Argued before WOODWARD, HOOKER, GAYNOR, RICH, and MILLER, JJ.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements, on the opinion in the Matter of Clement, as State Commissioner of Excise (decided herewith) 110 N. Y. Supp. 57.
